	<meta property="og:description" content="Slowly but surely, I am, it seems, taking up residence at 30,000 feet. Though Iâ€™m no jetsetter, income-wise or otherwise, my 2005â€”or the last eight months of it, anywayâ€”was punctuated by take-offs and landings. The airplane has become a central part of my personal geography. Falling in love with a New Yorker will do that to a Seattlite, and to her credit card. Itâ€™s been a big year for us both. I write this from seat 17F, somewhere between Newark and Seattle, with poppy seeds from an Absolute Bagel still stuck in my teeth. It was a full weekend to end a full year: we sampled pretzel croissants at City Bakery, slurped down hot apple cider with my old friend&hellip;" />
